## Application Class

**File:** `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/Application.h` / `Application.cpp`

### Singleton Pattern

`Application` is a singleton managed via a `static pg::U_Ptr<Application> s_Instance`.

```cpp
static Application& Create();   // constructs, calls Init(), returns reference
static Application& Get();      // returns *s_Instance
```

`Create()` is the only valid construction path. Direct construction (`Application()`) is `default` but leaves the object uninitialized; callers must go through `Create()`.

### `Application::Data` Inner Struct

All mutable state is grouped in `Application::Data m_Data`:

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `m_ImGuiLayer` | `S_Ptr<ImGuiLayer>` (non-test only) | ImGui overlay, pushed as a permanent overlay during `Init()` |
| `m_InputLayer` | `S_Ptr<InputLayer>` | Reserved input-layer slot (initialized via `Init()`) |
| `m_Window` | `S_Ptr<Window>` | Platform window; created in `Init()` |
| `m_Running` | `bool` | Loop sentinel; set to `false` by `OnWindowClose` |
| `m_Initialized` | `bool` | Guards `OnEvent` from firing before `Init()` completes |
| `m_ClockUptime` | `Clock` | Uptime since application start (not currently consumed by the loop) |
| `m_ClockFrameTime` | `Clock` | Restarted each frame to measure inter-frame delta |
| `m_LastFrameTime` | `Timestep` | Delta from the previous frame (milliseconds) |
| `m_LayerStack` | `LayerStack` | Ordered collection of client and engine layers |
| `m_Minimized` | `bool` | When `true`, event forwarding to ECS is skipped |

### Lifecycle

```
Log::Init()                         (EntryPoint.h main)
    └─> CreateApplication()         (client implements)
            └─> Application::Create()
                    └─> Init()
                            ├─> Window::Create()
                            ├─> World::Create()
                            ├─> RegisterSystem × 8 (see Built-in Systems)
                            ├─> Renderer::Init()
                            ├─> PushOverlay(ImGuiLayer)   [non-test only]
                            └─> m_Initialized = true
    └─> app.Run()
            └─> while(m_Running): UpdateApp()
~Application()
    └─> Shutdown()
            └─> LayerStack::Shutdown()  (calls OnDetach on all layers)
```

### Main Loop

```cpp
void Run();          // non-test only: spin on UpdateApp() while m_Running
void UpdateApp();    // measures inter-frame delta then calls Update(ts)
void Update(const Timestep& ts);
```

`Update(ts)` is the canonical per-frame body:

1. **Begin pass** — iterates `m_LayerStack` forward, calls `layer->Begin()` on every layer.
2. **Update pass** — iterates `m_LayerStack` forward, calls `layer->OnUpdate(ts)` on every layer.
3. **ECS update** — `pg::World::Get().Update(ts)` runs all registered ECS systems in dependency order.
4. **End pass** — iterates `m_LayerStack` forward, calls `layer->End()` on every layer.
5. **Window pump** — `m_Window->OnUpdate()` processes OS messages and swaps buffers.

In the `TESTS_ENABLED` build, `Run()` is removed; tests call `void TestUpdate(const Timestep& ts)` directly.

### Event Handling

```cpp
void OnEvent(const Event& e);
```

Called synchronously by the Window's event callback (registered during `Init()`). The method:

1. Guards on `m_Initialized`.
2. Dispatches `WindowResizeEvent` and `WindowCloseEvent` to the private handlers (`OnWindowResize`, `OnWindowClose`) regardless of minimization state.
3. When not minimized, translates every incoming `Event` subtype into the corresponding ECS event component via `World::EmplaceExternalEvent<T>()`. Event types covered:
   - `WindowResizeEventComponent`, `WindowCloseEventComponent`
   - `MouseButtonPressedEventComponent`, `MouseButtonReleasedEventComponent`
   - `MouseMovedEventComponent`, `MouseScrolledEventComponent`
   - `KeyPressedEventComponent`, `KeyReleasedEventComponent`, `KeyTypedEventComponent`
4. Any unrecognized `EventType` triggers `PG_CORE_ASSERT(false, "Event not implemented")`.

The two private handlers:

```cpp
bool OnWindowClose(const WindowCloseEvent& e);    // sets m_Running = false, returns false
bool OnWindowResize(const WindowResizeEvent& e);  // handles minimization, calls Renderer::OnWindowResize
```

Both return `false` (event is not consumed — it still propagates to the ECS as a component).

### Public API Summary

```cpp
static Application& Create();
static Application& Get();
Application();
virtual ~Application();

void Run();                                     // non-test only
void OnEvent(const Event& e);
void PushLayer(pg::S_Ptr<Layer> layer);         // calls layer->OnAttach()
void PushOverlay(pg::S_Ptr<Layer> layer);       // calls layer->OnAttach()
Window& GetWindow();
InputLayer& GetInputLayer();

// Test-only
const Data& GetData() const;
void TestUpdate(const Timestep& ts);
```

