## Layer and LayerStack

### Layer

**File:** `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/Layer.h` / `Layer.cpp`

Abstract base class for all engine and client layers. All methods are virtual no-ops by default.

```cpp
class PIGEON_API Layer
{
public:
    Layer(const std::string& name = "Layer");
    virtual ~Layer();

    virtual void OnAttach() {}                          // called by Application::PushLayer/PushOverlay
    virtual void OnDetach() {}                          // called by LayerStack::Shutdown
    virtual void OnUpdate(const Timestep& ts) {}        // called each frame (Update pass)
    virtual bool OnEvent(const Event& event) { return false; }  // not called by Application directly
    virtual void Begin() {}                             // called each frame before OnUpdate
    virtual void End() {}                               // called each frame after OnUpdate

    inline const std::string& GetName() const;
protected:
    std::string m_DebugName;
};
```

`OnEvent` on `Layer` is declared but **not dispatched by Application** — `Application::OnEvent` only forwards events to the ECS. If a concrete layer needs events it must obtain them from the ECS (e.g., by reading event components in `OnUpdate`). This is a deliberate architectural choice to route all events through the ECS.

### LayerStack

**File:** `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/LayerStack.h` / `LayerStack.cpp`

Maintains a single `std::vector<S_Ptr<Layer>>` split into two conceptual sections:

- **Layers** — occupy indices `[0, m_LayerInsertIndex)`. Inserted at `m_LayerInsertIndex` (pushed in front of all overlays).
- **Overlays** — occupy indices `[m_LayerInsertIndex, end)`. Always appended at the back.

This means layers inserted earlier via `PushLayer` sit before layers inserted later, and all overlays sit after all layers.

```cpp
void PushLayer(S_Ptr<Layer> layer);     // inserts at m_LayerInsertIndex, increments index
void PushOverlay(S_Ptr<Layer> overlay); // appends to back, does NOT increment index
void PopLayer(S_Ptr<Layer> layer);      // finds and erases, decrements m_LayerInsertIndex
void PopOverlay(S_Ptr<Layer> overlay);  // finds and erases, does NOT decrement index
void Shutdown();                        // calls OnDetach on all layers, clears vector
```

Iteration (`begin/end` and `rbegin/rend`) is exposed directly on the vector so range-for loops work. `Application::Update` iterates forward for all three passes (Begin, OnUpdate, End).

`LayerStack::Data` holds `m_Layers` and `m_LayerInsertIndex`. In test builds, `GetData()` exposes it for inspection.

