## Entry Point Pattern

**File:** `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Core/EntryPoint.h`

`EntryPoint.h` provides `main()` on Windows, but only when `TESTS_ENABLED` is not defined:

```cpp
extern pg::Application& pg::CreateApplication();

#ifndef TESTS_ENABLED
int main(int argc, char** argv)
{
    pg::Log::Init();
    PG_CORE_WARN("Initialized Log!");
    auto& app = pg::CreateApplication();
    app.Run();
}
#endif
```

`CreateApplication()` is declared in `pg` namespace but defined by the client. The SandboxApp pattern:

```cpp
// Sandbox2D.cpp
class Sandbox : public pg::Application { ... };

pg::Application& pg::CreateApplication()
{
    pg::Application& sandbox = Sandbox::Create();
    pg::World::Get().RegisterSystem(std::make_unique<sbx::ConfigLoaderSystem>());
    pg::World::Get().RegisterSystem(std::make_unique<sbx::SampleUISystem>());
    return sandbox;
}
```

The client subclasses `Application` purely as a tag (the `Sandbox` class adds no members or overrides). All behavior customization is done by registering additional ECS systems into the `World` after `Create()` completes, not by overriding `Application` methods.

