## Singleton Components

### `InputStateSingletonComponent`

```cpp
struct InputStateSingletonComponent {
    std::unordered_map<int, int> m_KeysPressed;   // key code -> frames held (1-based)
    std::unordered_map<int, int> m_KeysReleased;  // key code -> frames held when released (cleared each frame)
    std::vector<int>             m_KeysTyped;     // character codes received this frame (cleared each frame)
    glm::vec2                    m_MousePos;      // cursor position in window space
    glm::vec2                    m_MouseScroll;   // scroll delta this frame
};
```

### `EngineConfigSingletonComponent`

```cpp
struct EngineConfigSingletonComponent {
    pg::UUID m_DefaultQuadShaderID;
    pg::UUID m_DefaultTextShaderID;
    pg::UUID m_DefaultFontID;
};
```

### `ResourceMapSingletonComponent`

```cpp
struct ResourceMapSingletonComponent {
    std::unordered_map<pg::UUID, MappedTexture>        m_TextureMap;
    std::unordered_map<pg::UUID, S_Ptr<Shader>>        m_ShaderMap;
    std::unordered_map<pg::UUID, S_Ptr<Font>>          m_FontMap;
    std::unordered_map<pg::UUID, std::string>          m_UILayoutMap;
    pg::UUID                                           m_DefaultTexture;  // auto-generated UUID, always in m_TextureMap
};
```

`MappedTexture` is a pair of `{S_Ptr<Texture2D>, EMappedTextureType}` — the type tag distinguishes quad textures from font atlas textures.

### `OrthographicCameraComponent`

```cpp
struct OrthographicCameraComponent {
    float                    m_AspectRatio = 1.0f;
    float                    m_ZoomLevel   = 1.0f;
    pg::OrthographicCamera   m_Camera;                 // initialized as (0,0,0,0)
    bool                     m_Rotation    = false;
    glm::vec3                m_CameraPosition = {0,0,0};
    float                    m_CameraRotation          = 0.0f;
    float                    m_CameraTranslationSpeed  = 5.0f;
    float                    m_CameraRotationSpeed     = 180.0f;
    bool                     m_ReactsToInput           = false;
};
```

