## Event Component Types (ECS Bridge)

These structs live in `Core/` and are thin wrappers that carry platform event data into the ECS registry as one-frame-live entities (tagged also with `EventComponent`).

| Struct | Fields |
|---|---|
| `WindowCloseEventComponent` | `m_Dummy: bool` (marker only) |
| `WindowResizeEventComponent` | `m_Width: uint`, `m_Height: uint` |
| `KeyPressedEventComponent` | `m_KeyCode: int` |
| `KeyReleasedEventComponent` | `m_KeyCode: int` |
| `KeyTypedEventComponent` | `m_KeyCode: int` |
| `MouseButtonPressedEventComponent` | `m_Button: int` |
| `MouseButtonReleasedEventComponent` | `m_Button: int` |
| `MouseMovedEventComponent` | `m_MouseX: float`, `m_MouseY: float` |
| `MouseScrolledEventComponent` | `m_XOffset: float`, `m_YOffset: float` |
| `EventComponent` | `m_Dummy: bool` (base tag, auto-added alongside every event component by `World::EmplaceExternalEvent`) |
| `ApplicationEventComponent` | `m_Event: pg::Event` (present for structural completeness; not currently emitted) |

