## Utility Types

### `UUID`

**File:** `Core/UUID.h` / `UUID.cpp`

RFC-4122 version-4 (random) UUID backed by `std::array<unsigned char, 16>`.

```cpp
class PIGEON_API UUID {
public:
    UUID();                            // constructs null UUID (all-zero)
    UUID(std::string& uuidStr);        // parses "xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
    UUID(const char* uuidStr);

    static UUID Generate();            // random v4 UUID
    bool        IsNull()    const;
    std::string ToString()  const;     // returns canonical hyphenated hex string

    bool operator==(const UUID& other) const;
    bool operator!=(const UUID& other) const;

    static const UUID s_NullUUID;      // all-zero constant
};
```

`std::hash<pg::UUID>` is specialized via XOR-shift so UUIDs can be used as `unordered_map` keys. Parsing throws `std::invalid_argument` (via `PG_CORE_EXCEPT`) on malformed strings.

### `Log`

**File:** `Core/Log.h` / `Log.cpp`

Two spdlog color loggers: `"PGN"` (core/engine) and `"APP"` (client). Both set to `trace` level. `Log::Init()` is idempotent (guards on null).

Macros: `PG_CORE_{TRACE,INFO,WARN,ERROR,FATAL}` and `PG_{TRACE,INFO,WARN,ERROR,FATAL}`.

### `PlatformInput`

**File:** `Core/Input.h`

Abstract singleton providing platform key/mouse state queries. Concrete implementations live in `Platform/`. Systems interact with it only through `InputSystem`, which calls `PlatformInput::GetKeyCode()` / `GetMouseButtonCode()` to translate raw platform codes to engine constants.

### `Window`

**File:** `Core/Window.h`

Abstract interface for a platform window. Key members:

```cpp
static S_Ptr<Window> Create(const WindowProps& props = WindowProps()); // factory; impl in Platform/
void SetEventCallback(const EventCallbackFn& callback);  // called during Application::Init
virtual void OnUpdate() = 0;     // pumps OS messages; called at end of each frame
virtual unsigned int GetWidth()  const = 0;
virtual unsigned int GetHeight() const = 0;
virtual void SetVSync(bool)  = 0;
virtual bool IsVSync() const = 0;
virtual void* GetNativeWindow()    const = 0;
virtual void* GetGraphicsContext() const = 0;
```

Default `WindowProps`: title `"Pigeon Engine"`, 1280×720.

### Smart-Pointer Aliases and Utilities (`Core.h`)

```cpp
template<typename T> using U_Ptr = std::unique_ptr<T>;
template<typename T> using S_Ptr = std::shared_ptr<T>;

struct ReleaseDeleter { ... };     // calls ->Release() on destruction (COM objects)
template<typename T> class RAII_Ptr       { T* value; ~RAII_Ptr() { delete value; } };
template<typename T> class RAII_PtrRelease{ T* value; ~RAII_PtrRelease() { value->Release(); } };

template <auto EventFn, typename EventHandler>
auto BindEventFn(EventHandler* handler);  // creates a std::function wrapping a member function
```

Assertion macros:
- `PG_ASSERT(x, ...)` — client assertion; calls `PG_ERROR` and `__debugbreak()` (non-test).
- `PG_CORE_ASSERT(x, ...)` — engine assertion; same behavior.
- `PG_CORE_EXCEPT(x, ...)` — engine assertion that also throws `std::invalid_argument` (used in UUID parsing and config/resource loading).

