## Data Flow — Frame Lifecycle

```
OS / Platform
    │
    │ (OS input / window messages)
    ▼
Window::OnUpdate()  ──────────────────────────────► [last step each frame]
    │
    │  (fires EventCallbackFn)
    ▼
Application::OnEvent(Event&)
    │
    ├─ WindowClose / WindowResize ──► private handlers (set m_Running, call Renderer::OnWindowResize)
    │
    └─ All event types (when not minimized)
           │
           ▼
       World::EmplaceExternalEvent<XxxEventComponent>()
           │  (deferred: entity + EventComponent + XxxEventComponent created, flushed end-of-frame)
           ▼
       [visible next frame to ECS systems]

─────────────────── Per-Frame Update Sequence ────────────────────────────

1.  Clock::Restart() → Timestep (delta-time)
2.  LayerStack: all layers Begin()
3.  LayerStack: all layers OnUpdate(ts)
4.  World::Update(ts)
    ├─ Run each System::Update(ts) in dependency order
    │   ├─ CameraSystem        reads event components, writes OrthographicCameraComponent
    │   ├─ ConfigLoaderSystem  once: creates EngineConfigSingletonComponent
    │   ├─ InputSystem         reads event components, writes InputStateSingletonComponent
    │   ├─ ResourceManagerSystem once: creates ResourceMapSingletonComponent
    │   ├─ Renderer2DSystem    (Renderer module)
    │   ├─ UIControlSystem     (UI module)
    │   ├─ UIEventSystem       (UI module)
    │   └─ UIRenderSystem      (UI module)
    ├─ ClearEvents()           — destroy all entities tagged EventComponent
    └─ FlushDeferredRequests() — apply all emplace_deferred operations
5.  LayerStack: all layers End()
6.  Window::OnUpdate()         — OS pump + buffer swap
```

